This paper is primarily focused on improving the robustness of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in vision-related tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of architectural modifications to achieve this goal, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new layer for CNNs, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
